             <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">The descent of T=
om Ford Beauty is apparent in its product names. =E2=80=9CFucking Fabulous=
=E2=80=9D was the phenomenally successful scent that launched in 2017, and =
yet =E2=80=9CVanilla Sex,=E2=80=9D which came out last year, is like an <i>=
SNL </i>parody. This is likely the result of a series of subtle but signifi=
cant personnel changes. The brand=E2=80=99s executive director of editorial=
, involved in fragrance and makeup product names, stories, and positioning,=
 left in 2020. <b>John Demsey</b>, the veteran Lauder executive and archite=
ct behind the Tom Ford arrangement, got ousted over an Instagram post in 20=
22. Then Ford stepped down following the sale to ELC.<br/> <br/>To me, Laud=
er=E2=80=99s slowness to embrace TikTok as a marketing platform=E2=80=94an =
issue across their portfolio=E2=80=94was especially obvious at Tom Ford, wh=
ich failed to capitalize on viral products such as Soleil Lip
Blush, a $62 lip balm with gold flecks. This probably could have resulted i=
n years of relevance in their makeup category=E2=80=93=E2=80=93as we have s=
een with other luxury viral lip products such as Dior=E2=80=99s lip oil. Th=
ere=E2=80=99s also skincare, where there hasn=E2=80=99t been a new product =
launch in <i>years</i>, and I=E2=80=99m told that Lauder has steadily been =
reducing distribution since 2022. I=E2=80=99ve previously reported that ELC=
 C.E.O. <b>Fabrizio Freda</b>=E2=80=99s blanket approach to product=E2=80=
=93=E2=80=93i.e., forcing makeup brands to do skincare=E2=80=93=E2=80=93has=
 mostly backfired. An audacious makeup and fragrance brand launching a $450=
 =E2=80=9Ccreme concentrate=E2=80=9D? Come on.<br/> <br/>Back in 2018, I re=
member Ford telling me it took some cajoling to get Lauder to print =E2=80=
=9CFucking Fabulous=E2=80=9D on a bottle (conservative markets had watered-=
down versions that only implied profanity). That may be true, but even if F=
ord were still involved today, I=E2=80=99m not sure we would have gotten an=
other Black Orchid or Fucking Fabulous
fragrance, or a new makeup with the hype of the brand=E2=80=99s original li=
psticks. Arguably, it was Demsey=E2=80=99s exit that left Tom Ford Beauty e=
xposed. Without him, there=E2=80=99s no longer a dual corporate <i>and </i>=
brand-forward counterpart aligned with Ford=E2=80=99s vision who is also wi=
lling to be the intermediary with a CPG-minded Freda. Hard to imagine Demse=
y or Ford approving Vanilla Sex in a million years, either.<br/></td>
            </tr>
